            <bug_when>2009-03-30 13:47:14 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>Currently, an exception in a unit test has a chance of influencing subsequent tests since all test classes are loaded into a single application. This makes finding the actual cause of a problem harder and diminishes the usefulness of automated test reports since manual checking is required whenever there are multiple errors.

The test script could extract a list of test classes/packages from the Test Runner and load each individually before executing the tests.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
